Former Nasarawa State Governor Tanko Al-Makura yesterday said many progressive Northern elite worked hard to ensure that  Asiwaju Bola’s Tinubu clinched the All Progressives Congress(APC) presidential ticket because of his contributions to the enthronement of democracy in Nigeria. Al-Makura praised support groups in the North for their efforts in promoting Tinubu’s aspiration to become President Muhammadu Buhari’s successor. He spoke with members of support groups that teamed up with  Ahmed Tinubu Campaign Support Group (TCSG) in Lafia. The former governor, who is now the Senator representing Nasarawa’s South senatorial zone appealed to all those who supported other aspirants during the APC presidential primary to also come together under the TCSG umbrella.   Adegoroye, Umana, five others tipped as ministers     Ekiti: Dress rehearsal for next general elections     Buhari order security chiefs to rescue train attack victims…   The Senator told the group members that the Northern progressives were also impressed with  Tinubu’s records as governor of Lagos State between 1999-2007. He said that the coming together of the different support groups would enable them to work together to galvanise support for the APC presidential candidate. His words: “We are here to consolidate and get all the support groups together to wait for the direction of the campaign as would be directed by the central campaign organisation from the national level..” “We are also here to meet with the teeming numbers of support groups of other presidential aspirants in Nasarawa State. There are up to hundred support groups. We sincerely thank them for the efforts they have been doing in promoting the aspiration of Ahmed Tinubu  APC’s presidential flag bearer.” “We call on every APC member in the state to come and join the train in order to ensure a landslide victory come 2023 for the emergence of Ahmed Tinubu as Nigeria’s president.”